<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="535" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,726,1905]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1843,1869]" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[869,964,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">hamatus</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1022,1083,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="535">spina</emphasis>
, referring to the hooked apical spine of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
